id: pm-bkcv
title: "CodeFactor no-regression gate: complexity ceiling + ESLint suppressions baseline + Greptile in local CI/CD"
description: "Make 'no new CodeFactor issue' a mandatory guardrail so the codebase only improves. CodeFactor grade is A with ~155 issues dominated by 'Complex Method' (cyclomatic complexity) findings; the local ESLint parity used complexity max 260 (never fired). Lower the complexity ceiling to 17 (errors at CC>=18, matching CodeFactor's flagged range) and grandfather pre-existing violations in eslint-suppressions.json via ESLint native bulk suppressions. This blocks net-new per-file complexity debt while the baseline is maintained and pruned, but it is not a location-aware delta check for worsening an already-suppressed function. Fixing complex methods requires pruning stale suppressions, so the baseline can shrink toward zero — the path to a CodeFactor A+. This item wires the Greptile CLI reviewer into local CI/CD via scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.mjs (best-effort: fails on findings when authenticated, skips gracefully in token-less CI) and run-gates.mjs. Current committed suppression debt is 157; driving that to zero remains under this epic."
type: Chore
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: "area:ci","area:quality",codefactor,living-map,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-06-29T21:31:08.795Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-30T00:27:21.014Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: complexity ceiling lowered to 17 with committed eslint-suppressions.json baseline; pnpm lint passes on existing code and blocks net-new per-file complexity debt as the baseline is maintained; fixing a method forces a stale suppression prune where the file's baseline count drops (only-improve); greptile-review-gate.mjs added (best-effort skip when unauthenticated) and wired into run-gates.mjs + package.json; CONTRIBUTING documents the policy and its file/rule baseline semantics; all gates green; net A+ path documented.
parent: pm-92if
resolution: "Delivered a CodeFactor no-regression quality gate, reduced the committed complexity suppression baseline from 161 to 157, hardened the Greptile local review gate after AI review feedback, stabilized hosted coverage, and recorded full local/hosted validation evidence."
expected_result: "The repository blocks net-new local complexity debt through the committed ESLint suppression baseline, runs the Greptile review gate in local release checks, keeps package-author and temp-project workflows working, and has green PR checks before merge."
actual_result: "PR #405 implements the quality gate, Greptile gate, docs, tests, dependency refresh, and regression fixes; local lint/typecheck/coverage and temp-project smokes passed; hosted PR checks were green before PM closeout; remaining resolution warnings are pre-existing closed-item backlog outside this item."
comments[14]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-29T22:12:15.408Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: pruned CodeFactor complexity suppressions from 161 to 157 by simplifying repeatable metadata parsing, schema field command normalization, stable serialization equality, and telemetry error-code classification; refreshed typescript-eslint to 8.62.1 while keeping @types/node at the Node 22 support floor. Verification passed: npm install -g .; pm --version 2026.6.24; pnpm build; focused linked pm test run 6/6 passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 262 files, 5245 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines; pnpm lint; pnpm typecheck; pnpm contracts:check; pnpm security:scan; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; pnpm changelog:pm:check with pm-changelog 2026.6.27 and unchanged CHANGELOG.md; pm health --check-only clean; pm validate --check-history-drift clean with existing resolution-backfill warnings only; package doctor project deep clean; sentry-telemetry gate clean with zero critical/high Sentry issues and telemetry finish error rate 0.79%; isolated temp smoke passed init/create/update/files/docs/test run/close/release/health/validate plus declarative package scaffold npm test and package doctor. GitHub sweep found no open PRs at start, issue #374 still blocked by missing RELEASE_PAT, and no Dependabot/code scanning/secret scanning alerts."
  "2026-06-29T22:19:43.192Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile follow-up evidence: fixed stale eslint.config.mjs regeneration command, hardened greptile-review-gate so non-zero review exits cannot be reported clean even when output contains 'No review comments', and mapped the wrapper base option to the installed Greptile CLI's --branch flag. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts (10 tests), pnpm lint, pnpm typecheck."
  "2026-06-29T22:27:11.715Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile pre-push status: ran greptile review --help; initial committed review b53f47fd-26cf-4ab8-99da-f90a813844dc reported two findings and both were fixed. A rerun without layout returned the cached stale review text; a fresh layout-diff review 5b011ee8-ee9b-48bb-9bb0-2e4f440d7367 was dispatched but did not finish in the local polling window. Current diff confirms both original findings are fixed, and focused Greptile gate tests, lint, and typecheck pass; PR-side review agents will run on the pushed head."
  "2026-06-29T22:41:31.757Z",claude-code-agent,"AI review response evidence: addressed CodeRabbit, Gemini, and Cubic comments by clarifying file/rule suppression-baseline semantics in eslint.config.mjs and pm-bkcv, validating invalid/negative Greptile --timeout-ms values with a safe default, removing the unused fail import, printing Greptile review findings in human failure output, moving the clean-review regex after non-zero exit handling, and hoisting the stableValueEquals comparer list to module scope. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts tests/unit/core/shared/serialization-utils.spec.ts (17 tests), pnpm lint, pnpm typecheck."
  "2026-06-29T23:00:29.764Z",claude-code-agent,"CI coverage follow-up evidence: GitHub Gates (coverage) on run 28407762351 failed because the new Greptile human failure-output branch left branch coverage at 99.99% (scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.mjs line 50). Added a focused test for the empty-review-body failure path. Verification passed locally: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts (12 tests) and node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (262 files, 5248 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-06-29T23:25:23.361Z",claude-code-agent,"AI review response evidence: tightened Greptile review gate after latest Gemini feedback. Clean-review detection is now anchored to terminal output; nonzero review exits with findings output fail the gate instead of skipping; --branch is accepted as a wrapper alias while --base compatibility remains and both forward to Greptile's native comparison --branch flag. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts (15 tests before coverage fix); focused coverage run confirmed the spec passed but global partial coverage thresholds intentionally failed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 262 files, 5252 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines."
  "2026-06-29T23:25:31.422Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence correction: final Greptile gate focused suite is 16 tests after adding the nonzero findings --report-only branch case; final full coverage evidence remains node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passing 262 files, 5252 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines."
  "2026-06-29T23:37:23.462Z",claude-code-agent,"AI review response evidence: CodeRabbit follow-up addressed by using combined stdout/stderr output for the successful-exit Greptile findings failure path and adding stderr-only findings coverage. Also linked missing PR-scope files CONTRIBUTING.md, scripts/release/run-gates.mjs, and tests/unit/scripts/release/run-gates.spec.ts via pm files so the item manifest matches the full PR scope."
  "2026-06-29T23:42:52.131Z",claude-code-agent,"Verification evidence: CodeRabbit follow-up passed node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts (17 tests), pnpm lint, pnpm typecheck, and node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (262 files, 5253 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-06-29T23:52:40.285Z",claude-code-agent,"AI review response evidence: Cubic clean-review edge addressed by matching the Greptile clean sentinel on stdout only, so stderr progress/warnings do not turn a clean review into findings while stderr-only findings still fail. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/scripts/release/greptile-review-gate.spec.ts (18 tests), pnpm lint, pnpm typecheck, and node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (262 files, 5254 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-06-30T00:04:35.874Z",claude-code-agent,"CI follow-up: hosted Gates (coverage) failed on the context no-agenda markdown test because the helper default +1d deadline crossed into the July 1 query window after the runner clock reached 2026-06-30 UTC. Fixed the test seed to use an explicit out-of-window 2026-06-01 deadline and verified the focused regression locally."
  "2026-06-30T00:10:00.304Z",claude-code-agent,"Verification evidence: CI no-agenda regression fix passed focused node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/commands/context-command.spec.ts -t 'renders markdown guidance when agenda has no events'; pnpm lint; pnpm typecheck; and node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (262 files, 5254 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-06-30T00:13:37.996Z",claude-code-agent,"Greptile pre-push status: current-head local greptile review dispatched as 1f2aa176-ed51-4430-9701-f0c5ea93ad85 against main with layout diff/agent output, but the CLI timed out after 180s without returning findings. Proceeding with PR-side @greptileai retrigger on the pushed head plus green local lint/typecheck/coverage evidence."
  "2026-06-30T00:27:21.007Z",claude-code-agent,"Changelog evidence: regenerated CHANGELOG.md with pm-changelog 2026.6.27 after closing pm-bkcv so pnpm changelog:pm:check reflects the actual closed-item set."
